  "texts": [
    "Two p-sites a and a ′ are said to be isotopic if there is an isotopy between the two p-sites.Fact 1.5.12 Any canonical p-site is simple.",
    "Conversely any simple p-site a with base I is isotopic to ca(I, κ a).",
    "In fact π a is an isotopy of a to ca(I, κ).Proof.",
    "In view of 1.5.5, the parting function of ca(I, κ a) is injective, therefore the p-site ca(I, κ a) is simple.",
    "Conversely for any simple p-site a = ( (I, A,(A i))), the parting function π a is a bijection A → κ a."
